text:
A homonym is a trait or trait condition that occurs when you combine multiple alternative facts similar in form to the following.  For example, the following facts would be true: 
(1) I am an alcoholic;
(2) I am a government official;
(3) I am married to another woman;
(4) I am a relative of another person;
(5) I am a religious member;
(6) I am married to someone else.
